      "span_text": "The spectral analysis of the EEG recorded during cold pressor test has previously been shown to be a reproducible and valid method for the assessment of brain activity during experimental tonic pain.  The present study showed that in addition to conventional spectral analysis, eLORETA source localization of the EEG during resting state and experimental tonic pain (cold pressor test) also was reproducible in areas typically activated during pain."
